      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(os-summary): convert Darwin kernel version to macOS version in fallback",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #95145: When `sw_vers` is unavailable, `os.release()` returns the Darwin kernel version (e.g. `25.5.0`) which was used directly as the macOS version label, showing incorrect versions like \"macOS 25.5.0\" or (in some paths) \"macOS 15.x\" for Tahoe.\n\n**Fix**: Add `darwinToMacOS()` converter with known kernel→macOS mappings:\n- Darwin 24 → macOS 15 (Sequoia)\n- Darwin 25 → macOS 26 (Tahoe)\n- Darwin 20-23 → macOS 11-14 (darwinMajor - 9)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** macOS version reported incorrectly when sw_vers is unavailable\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS, Node v22.22.3, latest upstream/main\n- **Exact steps or command run:** `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/os-summary.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- **Evidence after fix:** 5/5 passed including new \"maps Darwin 25 to macOS 26 (Tahoe)\" test\n- **Observed result:** Darwin 25.5.0 maps to macOS 26.5.0, Darwin 24.1.0 maps to macOS 15.1.0\n- **What was not tested:** Live system without sw_vers (deterministic mapping)\n\nCloses #95145.\n\n---\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>",
